originalText.text: Very unprofessional and front desk dark-skinned lady is very rude with an attitude.   She wanted my physical insurance card which I didn't have it however I had a copy of it and she gave so much attitude about it.  What she gonna do make a copy anyway, I know I work in a doctors office.   Never Again.  Then she whispered to a young Spanish girl and she left to the store.  I told the Spanish girl To cancel my appointment because she is very rude.  She said I know.  And apologized for her rudeness.  I left.

originalText.text: I DO NOT RECOMMEND!!!!!! I Had a Referral for this clinic it was recommended by my gynecologist.It was my first time there so I  asked if a female was attending me, the assistant said it’s a male. Immediately I felt uncomfortable and asked the assistance if she could stay in the room with me, she said sure. When I was called in this other room ,The doctor sound upset &  told me that he had spoken to the assistant and didn’t like how I will have prefer a woman then said “look at me, I am a male”, The doctor became rude & unprofessional saying “go get checked by a female, I am a male”. He got up and left the room, didn’t even want to check my referral.

originalText.text: I have been going to Dr. Udo for over 12 years. The practice has added other services that naturally has increased the patient volume resulting in a little longer wait time. However, the staff is always courteous and helpful on visits and over the phone.

originalText.text: Wait times are ridiculous. Doesn't matter if you're early or not. I regret choosing this place as my ob for my first trimester. Doesn't matter what time I have arrived I always end up waiting 45mins and longer to see the Dr. I Have to call the front desk 10 times for an answer. Like what's the point. Set up a zoom call after rescheduling my appt earlier in the day and still had to wait over 45mins just for them to tell me I have to wait until the dr sees the rest of the patients. Can't win for loosing. Wouldn't recommend at all.

originalText.text: I’ve been going there for years. Maybe even a decade at this point. I wouldn’t go anywhere else. I’m actually really shocked at the other reviews. Everyone is so kind including Dr. Udo. We desperately need more amazing black doctors like him.
